subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
This new species is similar to 

Bioramix
(
Leipopleura
) 
miranda

sp. nov.
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the following characters (based on male): (1) pronotal surface shining and more strongly convex (weakly shining and more weakly in 

B. miranda

); (2) elytral surface with metallic sheen (without in 

B. miranda

); (3) protarsi narrower than apex of protibiae (as wide as in 

B. miranda

); (4) antennae and tarsi brown (black in 

B. miranda

); (5) base of parameres slightly wider than apex (much in 

B. miranda

).
